<![endif]--><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s an=C2=A0<em>approvi=
ng </em>picture; that=E2=80=99s, like, =E2=80=9Cthis thing is a thing that =
we could see our way to allowing.=E2=80=9D You don=E2=80=99t include a pict=
ure of BlockFi=E2=80=99s proposed product if you think the proposal doesn=
=E2=80=99t work.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And it is in both sides=E2=
=80=99 interests to make this work: BlockFi of course wants to have a profi=
table lending product, but the SEC also wants to demonstrate that it can re=
gulate crypto activity. =E2=80=9CWe will ban all crypto activity=E2=80=9D i=
s not, I think, a particularly viable approach for the SEC to take at this =
point. The SEC wants to send a message along the lines of =E2=80=9Clots of =
crypto things are securities and thus subject to securities regulation, but=
 that=E2=80=99s fine because securities regulation is totally workable for =
crypto things.=E2=80=9D So=C2=A0making securities regulation work for a pop=
ular crypto product=C2=A0is a goal for the SEC too.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">We are still in the very early stages of crypto regulation in the =
U.S., and if you are a crypto firm you have to think a bit about the meta-r=
egulatory landscape.=C2=A0There seem to be roughly three approaches:</p><ol=
 style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Try to make yourself as immune as poss=
ible to U.S. regulation by setting up abroad, running your firm as a decent=
ralized entity with no one for the SEC to yell at, staying anonymous, and d=
oing whatever egregious things you want. So far this seems to work! Not eve=
ryone will want to move abroad and be anonymous though, and this approach s=
eems to carry some big risks.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Try =
to be as law-abiding as possible, consult with the relevant U.S. authoritie=
s before doing anything adventurous, and make your case to the regulators f=
or rules that you think will be good for crypto. This sounds good, but I am=
 not sure it=C2=A0<em>works</em>. When Coinbase Global Inc., a U.S. public =
company, wanted to launch a lending product like BlockFi=E2=80=99s, the SEC=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26719940.285603/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMDgvbGVu=
