t clearly hoped would spark a conversation in Washington about how best to =
build a new crypto regulatory framework for crypto; I don=E2=80=99t think a=
nyone has mentioned it since.=C2=A0When Facebook (now Meta Platforms Inc.) =
wanted to launch a stablecoin, it put on a big show of working with regulat=
ors, which gave regulators lots of chances to say no, which they did, and n=
ow=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26719940.2=
