he Bloomberg Billionaires Index, and rewarding investors in his flagship fu=
nd with a 35% gain. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Avis wage=
r is unusual for him. It=E2=80=99s the largest and longest he=E2=80=99s mad=
e, and the only one where he -- or anyone else at the firm -- sits on a com=
pany=E2=80=99s board. Hedge funds generally avoid board seats because that =
limits when they can buy and sell shares. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">The jump in Sarma=E2=80=99s net worth was particularly large becau=
se the investment is spread across several of the firm=E2=80=99s portfolios=
, and he personally owns about 90% of one fund that only holds the Avis sta=
ke.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imagine being Sarma and si=
tting down to write your investor letters for 2021. You start with the flag=
ship fund: =E2=80=9CI am happy to report that we were up 35% this year. Our=
